### 1. Introduction and Directions to Appendix Files ###

# Before running the seq2science pipeline it needed to be initiated by the following bash code:

conda activate seq2science
seq2science init atac-seq

# These commands generate two files - samples.tsv - where all the information about the fastqs, assembly, and replicate information was added. config.yaml - contains custom instructions modifying the pipeline to the current needs.
# The samples.tsv file is present in: "ATACseq - 1.1. Seq2science - Samples.tsv"
# The config.yaml file is present in "ATACseq - 1.2. Seq2science - Config.yaml"

# After the two files were modified and saved in the working directory, the following line of code was used to run the pipeline

nice -n10 seq2science run atac-seq --cores 20
